Epigyne with copulatory openings in small cup-shaped ridges (
Fig. 65
); copulatory ducts thin, initially curving mesally, then directed posteriorly along midline, looping dorsally and laterally before entering lateral teardropshaped primary spermathecae along their interior margin; bursae globular, slightly smaller than primary spermathecae (
Fig. 66
).

Palpal femur with short thumb tip-like ventral apophysis; patella with small, broad subtriangular retrolateral ridge; tibia with tibial apophysis short and triangular in ventral view, triangular and proximally directed in retrolateral view; embolus shorter and narrower than in congeners, tip slightly bent and directed retrodistally (
Figs 67–70
).
